</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C352655BFF864135FF72FB89FAE3B72C" box="[151,1362,1105,1130]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF72FB89FAE3B72C" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" box="[151,1362,1105,1130]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF864135FF72FB89FEA0B72C" bold="true" box="[151,273,1105,1130]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF864135FEFDFB89FE15B72C" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[280,420,1105,1130]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oscinellinae">Oscinellinae</taxonomicName>
with an apicoventral, hind-tibial spur, trapezoidal scutellum and long slender arista.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C352655BFF864135FF22FBADFE1DB4A8" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF22FBADFCB9B604" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF864135FF22FBADFEE8B7C8" bold="true" box="[199,345,1141,1166]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF864135FE85FBADFE5FB7C8" box="[352,494,1141,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF864135FE1FFBADFD3BB7C8" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[506,650,1141,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Oscinellinae">Oscinellinae</taxonomicName>
. Vertex rounded in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF864135FC1BFBADFBE3B7C8" box="[1022,1106,1141,1166]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–43" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[188,1391,389,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,303,1899]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 39–43. Goniaspis rubra. 39. Head: lateral; 40. Antenna; 41. Scutellum, dorsal; 42. Male genitalia, posterior; 43. Male genitalia, lateral. (42–43 reproduced with permission from Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler, 2009). Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439429/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
); frontal triangle shining and bare; frons microtomentose; cephalic chaetotaxy: long peristomal bristles, cruciate postocellar bristles, cruciate short ocellar bristles, long outer vertical bristles, interfrontal setulae long and on margin of frontal triangle, orbital bristles reclinate, of equal size; eye sparsely and microscopically pubescent; gena narrow, vibrissal angle rounded, indistinct; face flat, wide, carina absent; first flagellomere reniform, higher than wide, arista longer than width of frons, and slender (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF864135FE8BFAF1FE73B604" box="[366,450,1321,1346]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–43" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[188,1391,389,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,303,1899]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 39–43. Goniaspis rubra. 39. Head: lateral; 40. Antenna; 41. Scutellum, dorsal; 42. Male genitalia, posterior; 43. Male genitalia, lateral. (42–43 reproduced with permission from Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler, 2009). Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439429/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); proboscis and palpus short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF22FA96FE96B5C0" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Scutum square, as wide as long; thoracic chaetotaxy: 1 anterior, 1 posterior notopleurals, 1 postsutural supraalar bristle, 1 dorsocentral bristle; scutellum usually flat dorsally, trapezoidal, usually wider than long (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF864135FAC1FAA9FAC9B6CC" box="[1316,1400,1393,1418]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–43" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[188,1391,389,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,303,1899]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 39–43. Goniaspis rubra. 39. Head: lateral; 40. Antenna; 41. Scutellum, dorsal; 42. Male genitalia, posterior; 43. Male genitalia, lateral. (42–43 reproduced with permission from Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler, 2009). Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439429/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
); 1 pair apical scutellar bristles on small tubercles, 1 or 2 pairs of lateral scutellar bristles; thoracic pleurites bare except for a row of setulae on katepisternum. Wing long, narrow, hyaline, second costal sector equal to or shorter than third costal sector, distance between crossvein r-m and dm-cu 2.4 times length of dm-cu, anal angle reduced, alula small, much longer than wide; veins pale; halter white. Legs long and slender; male femoral organ present as two rows of 3–5 tubercles; small, apical ventral spur on mid tibia; hind tibial spur present, usually apical, length usually more than twice diameter of hind tibia; tibial organ oval, sometimes very narrow, 0.2 to 0.25 times length of hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF22F949FBCBB588" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Abdominal tergites setulose laterally and with sparse setae posteriorly, mostly microtomentose; sternites slender, with sparse setae; male spiracles 
<quantity id="4CB09B35FF864135FD82F96DFD1FB588" box="[615,686,1717,1742]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" metricValueMax="1.27" metricValueMin="0.762" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 in</quantity>
membrane near lateral margin of tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF22F901FB4DB4C4" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Male postabdomen: pregenital sclerites narrow; spiracles 6 and 
<quantity id="4CB09B35FF864135FC4EF902FC68B5B4" box="[939,985,1753,1778]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
membrane ventral to lateral margin of dorsal sclerite; epandrium rounded, usually higher than long in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF864135FBC1F925FBCBB450" box="[1060,1146,1789,1814]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–43" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[188,1391,389,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,303,1899]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 39–43. Goniaspis rubra. 39. Head: lateral; 40. Antenna; 41. Scutellum, dorsal; 42. Male genitalia, posterior; 43. Male genitalia, lateral. (42–43 reproduced with permission from Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler, 2009). Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439429/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) and wider than high in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="13732A55FF864135FEA3F8F9FE2BB47C" box="[326,410,1825,1850]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–43" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[188,1391,389,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,303,1899]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 39–43. Goniaspis rubra. 39. Head: lateral; 40. Antenna; 41. Scutellum, dorsal; 42. Male genitalia, posterior; 43. Male genitalia, lateral. (42–43 reproduced with permission from Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler, 2009). Abbreviations: cer—cercus; epd—epandrium; sur—surstylus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439429/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
); surstylus simple, clavate or quadrate; hypandrium closed posteriorly; pregonite fused with postgonite, weakly sclerotized; basiphallus elongate, weakly sclerotized; distiphallus short, membranous; phallapodeme simple; phallic 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF864135FE02F8B1FD94B4C4" box="[487,549,1897,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Anatrichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guide">guide</taxonomicName>
sclerotized; cercus small, triangular, projecting posteroventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF22F855FC77B4E0" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" box="[199,966,1933,1958]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female terminalia not modified, cerci separate, cylindrical, setulose.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF864135FF22F869FE1DB4A8" blockId="20.[151,1436,1105,2030]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF864135FF22F869FE46B48C" bold="true" box="[199,503,1969,1994]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF864135FD75F86AFCB3B48F" authorityName="Duda, Melanochaeta Bezzi" authorityYear="1930" box="[656,770,1970,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF864135FD75F86AFCB3B48F" box="[656,770,1970,1993]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Goniaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded only from the Neotropical region including the Caribbean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C352655BFF874134FF22FF4FFD4DB3BE" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF736D0FF874134FF22FF4FFD4DB3BE" blockId="21.[151,1437,151,248]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF874134FF22FF4FFE8AB3F6" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C484D53FF874134FEA6FF40FE04B3E9" authorityName="Duda, Melanochaeta Bezzi" authorityYear="1930" box="[323,437,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Goniaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93CEAC2FF874134FEA6FF40FE04B3E9" box="[323,437,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Goniaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has recently been revised (Mlynarek &amp; Wheeler 2009). As a result of this analysis, the generic limits have been expanded to include an undescribed Puerto Rican species with a short hind tibial spur. That species is the sister group to the rest of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
